    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Drawing technique used to render three dimensions in a two-dimensional medium. Depth is represented by rendering all lines in the drawing so that they disappear to one or more points. This term is often used when representing architectural and spatial elements, such as buildings, cityscapes, streets, and other structures. It may also be applied to the rendering of objects in the context of industrial design.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
